    "body": "<span class=\"solution-visible-txt\">All submissions for this problem are available.</span><p>A monkey wants to climb a tree, but the problem is that he is not good climber. After climbing <b>N</b> distance, he slips by <b>M</b> distance. So he didn't know how many exact step he needs to climb the tree. Help him to find number of steps required to climb whole tree.</p>\n<h3>Input</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>The first line of the input contains an integer <b>T</b> denoting the number of test cases. The description of <b>T</b> test cases follows.</li>\n<li>Each test cases of single line contains <b>H</b>, <b>N</b>, <b>M</b> denoting height of a tree, climb distance of a jump, slip distance respectively.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\u00c2 </p>\n<h3>Output</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>For each test case, output a single line containing number of steps required to climb whole tree.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\u00c2 </p>\n<h3>Constraints</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>T</b> \u2264 <b>500</b></li>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>H</b> \u2264 <b>10<sup>3</sup></b></li>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>M</b> &lt; <b>N</b> \u2264 <b>10</b></li>\n<li>Monkey can grab top tightly so at top monkey won't slide.</li>\n<li>All answer must be up to 2 decimal place.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\u00c2 </p>\n<h3>Example</h3>\n<pre><b>Input:</b>\n2\n10 3 2\n15 5 2\n\n<b>Output:</b>\n8.00\n4.60\n\n</pre><p>\u00c2 </p>\n<h3>Explanation</h3>\n<p><b>Example case 1:</b> Monkey will jump three distance and slides two distance, so at one jump he can cover up to 1 distance, continuing in same way up to step 7 location of monkey is at 7, so in next monkey will jump 3 distance and reaches the top making it 8th step.</p>\n<p><b>Example case 2:</b> Here up to step 4 monkey's location is at 12. In next jump monkey will reach at 17, but we need to reach up to 15 so we will consider only 3 distance of jump so it is 3/5 of normal jump making this step 0.60 and final answer is 4.60.</p>\n",
